CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 10, 1962, pg. A23, reads: "NAACP Awards - At the NAACP award and planning meeting in Downtown YWCA, Saturday, awards were presented to several persons. Show [sic] are (left to right), Mrs. Mildred Bond, National Life Membership secretary, who presented awards to Robert Lee, F. F. chairman, Monongahela Valley branch; Louis E. Waller, president, Washington, Pa., branch;  Mrs. Coretta Ogburn, membership chairman of the Pittsburgh branch of the NAACP, and Lucille Black, National Membership secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mildred Bond, Robert Lee, Louis E. Waller, Coretta Ogburn, and Lucille Black holding NAACP award plaques
